<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Hard to be perfect, but its a burden I've learned to live with.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ramshutu>ramshutu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bananaman</span><br>  Posts: 783<br> <font color=#330000>(7/30/03 3:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=897.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.johnsrealmonline.com/classicnick/bananaman/Image33.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Dead Pool</span><hr size=1> The future system is intended to do the following :<br>
<br>
o Use experts in different field asside from intelligence try and make decent guesses as to what is likely to happen.<br>
<br>
o Get an alternative risk assesment (if you have a high alert, and a high probability on the futures market, something may be up).<br>
<br>
o Help the Pentagon plan for events it cannot really judge.<br>
<br>
Futures investors make this shit their business. And while they won't have the hundreds and thoasand reports of the pentagon, they will have their own legitimate sources of information and may well pick up on information said, or deliberatley left unsaid that may not be attainable by the pentagon.<br>
<br>
Bad points?<br>
<br>
o It'll encourage terrorists to change their plans and slip away!<br>
- Bullshit, it will do this less than the current security threat 'Levels' in force today<br>
- If they change their plans, it's good, because they are not commiting terrorist acts.<br>
- If the pentagon knows about these terrorists existance, they will not slip away.<br>
- If the pentagon didn't, the change of plans will give the pentagon more chance of detecting them AND has averted an incident that the pentagon wasn't aware of.<br>
<br>
o It'll encourage terrorists to commit more acts!<br>
- Bullshit, how? <br>
- Any terrorist clever enough to want to bet on futures, will invest in oil instead. We all know they can make far more money off a sky rocketing oil price after an incident.<br>
- The list of investors is closed.<br>
<br>
Ghoulish it may be, a bit disgusting possibly. It's a damned good idea as :<br>
<br>
o It will increase the layers of prediction currently in place, and may well be reasonably accurate.<br>
o It will increase the likelihood of the country being prepared for something happening<br>
o It will increase the ability to predict what is going to happen in the future.<br>
