So, this is just par for the course, but I was rather surprised that this one even came about.  Tom Dashel (who I actualy am not very fond of) called this an insult to the people of 9/11, barbaric, and an embarasment to the American comunity by its mere existance (slight paraphrase).  The idea of purchasing futures is a good point, but letting investors make money when they are right through some perverted form of a betting pool is disgusting at best.  Create yet another government offiice that works like this, perhaps I will not be AS repulsed by it, but treating terrorism like a roulette wheel at a casino is an insult.  How would you feel knowing that someone you know won X dollars because they correctly predicted a car bombing that killed your mother while she was buying vegatables in the outdoor market?<br>
<br>
I did hear a rumor that this was some April Fools joke; I only hope some credibility is found to this. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=316564" target="top">Tib</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
