<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Hard to be perfect, but its a burden I've learned to live with.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=surrealle>Surrealle</A> at: 7/30/03 8:55 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gundarkviresdator>Gundark Viresdator</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#330000>(7/30/03 9:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=897.topic&index=36>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.eqguild.net/guilds/harmonic%20chaos/aurora.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Dead Pool</span><hr size=1> The real paradox about the &quot;intelligence&quot; business is that the victories are rarely ever heard about.  The failures, of course, we still talk about one year, ten months, and nineteen days later.  If a system like this one had managed to foil the Nine-Eleven attacks, it most certainly would not have been front page news.  <br>
<br>
*Maybe* page 14.  <br>
<br>
Of the business section.<br>
<br>
If at all.  <br>
<br>
I am certain that we've probably won a lot of small battles, or maybe huge battles on this &quot;War on Terrorism.&quot;  Most likely, many of them were not won by the heroics of some James Bond type, even, but some poor schmuck at Langley VA examining satellite photos. Or maybe analyzing a cargo manifest on some ship.  He noticed something odd... he made a call to the sheriff or master of the port and someone was questioned... Hell, they didn't even need to question anyone, just be visible snooping around.  Then the bad guys just scrapped or postponed their plans because they saw that the authorities were getting a little too close for comfort.<br>
<br>
I guess you could say that the successes drive them further underground, to become more stealthy.  That's probably true.  But the more sophisticated the &quot;bad guys'&quot; methods get, the same goes for the &quot;good guys'&quot; countermeasures.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is, this scheme might have worked, it might not have.  We would not really have known one way or the other.  It would still be morally dubious at best.  <p>Hi, my name is Gundark, and I'm an alchemyholic.<br>
